fields.Title: Dolores Dei: ""Do you know how much it hurts me t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you know how much it hurts me to hear you say that?" She sounds downright angry. "I'm shit, you made me shit... I can't do this any more. I can't make you *insane* and *shit* any more, I can't let you turn me into a bad person. I have to go..."

fields.Title: You: ""What's in the bag?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What's in the bag?"

fields.Title: Dolores Dei: ""Exactly, now..." She glances over..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Exactly, now..." She glances over her shoulder. You hear distant traffic. An airship passes overhead, dogs bark somewhere.

fields.Dialogue Text: "The poetry thing is not going to help. It's only going to make things worse. I *really* have to go... I don't even know how you got here."

fields.Title: You: ""But you said I have a vast soul an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "But you said I have a vast soul and you will always come back to it."

fields.Title: You: ""Don't go...""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Don't go..."

fields.Dialogue Text: "See?" Her eyes widen. "It just takes some time. For you, it will take something like... twenty years maybe? It was hard for me too. I used to think I couldn't *live* without you..." She looks you straight in the eye -- her irises are light blue, flecked with green.

fields.Dialogue Text: "Insane... how?"

fields.Title: You: ""Let's try to return Revachol to th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's try to return Revachol to the likeness of the holy sun in the sky -- but only *twice*. The third time, let's abandon it to debauched homo-sexuals!"

fields.Title: You: ""Let's try inventing the future *tw..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Let's try inventing the future *twice* and if it doesn't work -- abandon it and live on welfare? Is that how we should do *everything*?"

fields.Title: You: ""No. I meant *mourning*. I'm grievi..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No. I meant *mourning*. I'm grieving -- but you're not even dead."

fields.Title: Suggestion: "A form of communication where words..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A form of communication where words have failed?

You: ""You're right, yes. So *paranoid* o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You're right, yes. So *paranoid* of me. There is no antagonism between us."

fields.Title: You: ""Do what?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do what?"

fields.Title: Dolores Dei: ""Months already. Soon it will be ye..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Months already. Soon it will be years. Every season that passes the lights get less clear. I sit there, in Mirova -- in the holy gratitude of my bliss -- I put my hand on my belly and *smile...*"

fields.Title: Dolores Dei: "Nothing, just pillows against you...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nothing, just pillows against you. Unresponsive... but for the taste of apricots.

fields.Title: Dolores Dei: "The mysterious smile on her lips ke..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The mysterious smile on her lips keeps stretching wider, as if she's forgotten you're there. In some great and calming thought. Then she notices you -- and it's immediately gone.

fields.Title: Dolores Dei: ""...""

fields.Dialogue Text: "It's here, Harry." She looks around. "We are *on* Voyager Road. At the end of it -- three hundred metres from the stop. We used to come here to rent videos."

fields.Title: You: ""Would you say you haven't behaved..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Would you say you haven't behaved like a mass murderer -- with me?"

fields.Title: Empathy: "You couldn't make her lungs glow an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You couldn't make her lungs glow anyway, only cry. And maybe not even that anymore.

fields.Dialogue Text: "No, Harry. Not yet. There is one more thing you have to see..." She slides her hands down her chest, and onto her lower stomach. And smiles.

fields.Dialogue Text: A warm gust wraps her gown around her waist and between her thighs.

fields.Title: Authority: "You have sworn a holy oath Harry. S..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You have sworn a holy oath Harry. She herself begged you to not let her go.

fields.Title: Drama: "Lies, sire! She cannot but love you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Lies, sire! She cannot but love you. She  has said so a hundred times.

fields.Title: Dolores Dei: ""See you tomorrow.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "See you tomorrow."

fields.Title: Dolores Dei: ""I'm suffocatingly beautiful. And y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm suffocatingly beautiful. And young. And I smell of tutti frutti chewing gum -- like I did that time when I asked you for forgiveness. After leaving you the first time, so long ago..."

fields.Title: You: ""Look at my face. Can you not see h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Look at my face. Can you not see how *hard* I am?" (Point to your diamond hard fascist face.)

fields.Title: You: ""You have a new guy, right? He's fu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You have a new guy, right? He's fucking *poor* compared to me. I'm gonna INCINERATE him. I have more money than any human being should have. It's SCARY how rich I am. I’m richer than GOD!"

fields.Title: Dolores Dei: "She doesn't know what to say."
fields.Dialogue Text: She doesn't know what to say.

fields.Title: Dolores Dei: ""Wow -- see? A new species..." She..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wow -- see? A new species..." She smiles. It's another sad smile, with knitted brows.

fields.Title: Savoir Faire: "Oh god, whatever you do, don't try..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Oh god, whatever you do, don't try to kiss her yet -- not after that, you're still reeling... you'll fall over if you try it now...

fields.Title: Dolores Dei: ""That's it, yes," she looks up from..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "That's it, yes," she looks up from her toes. "We've talked about it a million times. You will get over it, just like I did. People do. Things will get good for you again..."

fields.Title: You: ""I'm not getting over it *at all*!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm not getting over it *at all*!"

fields.Title: Empathy: "She keeps her shoulders squared and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: She keeps her shoulders squared and her back straight but it's clear you're still making her sad.

fields.Title: Dolores Dei: ""It's okay.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's okay."

fields.Dialogue Text: "Other people get sad too, but not like you, you stay down for too long -- and if you're not down, you're up, running around asking questions. Millions of questions..."
